              "displayName": "Bikas Saha",
              "active": true,
              "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
            },
            "body": "Motivation? Just a note : the RM state store is not designed for high throughput high churn operations. That probably is not the case here.\nHowever, I would like to put this in the context of general configuration management (say scheduler queue configs) in YARN. [~vinodkv] was mentioning the necessity of maintaining a synced version of such configuration so that when RM's fail over then they continue to have the same view of the cluster. Will the intent of the jira be covered by this?",
            "updateAuthor": {
              "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=bikassaha",
              "name": "bikassaha",
              "key": "bikassaha",
